WEBVTT

00:00.080 --> 00:05.440
What do you call it when a retired Air Force general, one who once ran the most notorious

00:05.440 --> 00:10.320
lab in UFO history, vanishes from his house in broad daylight?

00:10.320 --> 00:15.480
The general was involved with the Pentagon's most advanced aerospace research.

00:15.480 --> 00:21.080
When the NASA material scientist behind a breakthrough rocket engine alloy disappears

00:21.080 --> 00:23.600
30 feet from her friend on a hike.

00:23.600 --> 00:29.760
She was right behind them, 30 feet behind them, and then she disappeared.

00:29.760 --> 00:37.080
And one of MIT's top plasma physicists is gunned down outside his own front door.

00:37.080 --> 00:42.720
This many top scientists getting killed or going missing in just under a year looks like

00:42.720 --> 00:44.200
a major red flag.

00:44.200 --> 00:50.040
Who were the first people the Israelis killed in Iran when they went in?

00:50.040 --> 00:54.080
The first thing you do is kill your scientists.

00:54.080 --> 00:58.360
It's the kind of thing that sounds like the Chinese science fiction book, The Three-Body

00:58.360 --> 00:59.360
Problem.

00:59.360 --> 01:04.480
A world where scientists don't just make discoveries, but become the front line of a war they don't

01:04.480 --> 01:06.680
even know they're in.

01:06.680 --> 01:11.640
A world where the future rests on some of the most important minds on Earth.

01:11.640 --> 01:14.600
And those minds start disappearing.

01:14.600 --> 01:18.680
Except here, the names and the people behind them are real.

01:18.680 --> 01:24.800
Cassius went missing after taking lunch to her teenage daughter at a cafe in Taos Plaza.

01:24.800 --> 01:30.400
Some of them were very important people, and we're going to look at it over the next session.

01:30.400 --> 01:36.160
What we're looking at might not just be geopolitics in the dark or pressure coming from nation states,

01:36.160 --> 01:41.600
but from an unseen force shaping our timeline from somewhere above it, and a hidden struggle

01:41.600 --> 01:45.680
over who gets to control humanity's next leap.

01:45.680 --> 01:48.680
Or maybe none of these cases are connected.

01:48.680 --> 01:53.120
It's really sensitive stuff, and I'm not a big believer in coincidences.

01:53.120 --> 01:58.580
So tonight we're following the trail through missing scientists, murdered physicists, defense

01:58.580 --> 02:04.660
world gatekeepers, in this strange shadowland that forms wherever advanced knowledge becomes

02:04.660 --> 02:06.920
too dangerous to leave walking around.

02:06.920 --> 02:24.340
There's a state that researchers called hypnagogia, that threshold between waking and sleep where

02:24.340 --> 02:27.040
the brain is doing something genuinely unusual.

02:27.040 --> 02:32.320
The kind of thing that comes up in remote viewing accounts or other out-of-body experiences.

02:32.320 --> 02:37.320
And honestly, some of the most fascinating conversations I've had on this show.

