Again, that's helixsleep.com slash jessemichaels, michaels with no A.

04:14.440 --> 04:35.180
The trail begins in Albuquerque, New Mexico, in the shadow of Sandia Mountains.

04:35.180 --> 04:41.400
It's February 27th, 2026, a late Friday morning on Quail Run Court.

04:42.140 --> 04:47.880
Neil McCaslin, a 68-year-old retired Air Force general, is at home in a quiet neighborhood

04:47.880 --> 04:50.460
at the edge of the Cibola National Forest.

04:50.460 --> 04:53.640
A repairman sees him at the house around 10 a.m.

04:54.120 --> 05:00.140
Then, about an hour later, around 11.10 a.m., his wife leaves for a medical appointment.

05:00.140 --> 05:04.520
At 12.04, barely an hour after that, she's back home.

05:06.440 --> 05:08.640
But her husband is gone.

05:08.960 --> 05:14.280
Left behind are his prescription glasses, his phone, which had been switched off, and his

05:14.280 --> 05:14.940
smartwatch.

05:15.100 --> 05:18.640
All the things that would make him trackable in the 21st century.

05:19.120 --> 05:25.280
But what's missing is a red backpack, his wallet, and a .38 caliber revolver with its

05:25.280 --> 05:25.700
holster.

05:25.700 --> 05:27.360
Not the best combination.

05:28.320 --> 05:34.420
At 3.07, his wife Susan reports him missing, and the official police investigation begins.

05:34.660 --> 05:40.780
In a newly released 911 call, she tells the dispatcher he's been gone for about three hours.

05:41.120 --> 05:45.680
I have some indication that he must have planned not to be found.

05:45.900 --> 05:51.220
She said he changed his clothes, and appears to be on foot, since none of their cars or bikes

05:51.220 --> 05:51.780
were missing.

05:51.780 --> 05:56.720
She also tells dispatch that he's been dealing with some medical issues, and that both of

05:56.720 --> 06:01.980
them were seeing a doctor for anxiety, lack of sleep, and short-term memory problems.

06:02.380 --> 06:06.200
In fact, it was the same doctor she had seen earlier that day.

06:06.400 --> 06:11.780
But Susan chalked the health issues up to garden-variety things that you face in old age.

06:11.960 --> 06:15.720
She never thought that Neil would actually act in a way to harm himself.

06:15.720 --> 06:21.160
Saying if his brain and body keeps deteriorating, he didn't want to live like that.

06:21.800 --> 06:27.980
But it seemed to me that was just a, man, I hate how this is going kind of thing.

06:28.220 --> 06:31.920
A comment like that would naturally raise concerns about self-harm.

06:32.000 --> 06:36.940
But whether that was a real risk or just a throwaway comment on an off day, we don't

06:36.940 --> 06:37.660
actually know.

06:37.660 --> 06:42.640
When the police asked about the weapons, she said that her husband had a gun safe with

06:42.640 --> 06:48.060
multiple pistols and rifles, but at that moment, couldn't tell whether anything was actually

06:48.060 --> 06:48.460
missing.

06:48.820 --> 06:52.720
Although now we know that one of his .38 calibers was, in fact, gone.

06:53.040 --> 06:55.420
The next day, a silver alert goes out.

06:55.820 --> 07:00.320
This is the kind of statewide alert issued when authorities think a missing person might be

07:00.320 --> 07:02.700
disoriented or cognitively impaired.

07:02.700 --> 07:07.820
New Mexico state statute doesn't require any kind of formal diagnosis.

07:08.400 --> 07:12.700
Given what Susan had already told the police, that was enough to trigger it.

07:12.780 --> 07:18.280
But even with those reported issues, McCaslin still doesn't fit the profile of a man who

07:18.280 --> 07:20.000
just wandered into a canyon.

07:20.260 --> 07:23.360
Investigators say he's still highly intelligent and capable.

07:23.620 --> 07:28.420
Friends say that the week before he disappeared, McCaslin cycled 60 miles.

07:28.860 --> 07:30.680
He hiked those very foothills.

07:31.020 --> 07:31.740
He biked them.

07:31.740 --> 07:33.300
He knew every trail.

07:33.940 --> 07:38.640
This wasn't a man losing his bearings, but the kind of guy who could out-ski most millennials.

07:39.080 --> 07:41.200
This was also a town he knew by heart.

07:41.440 --> 07:46.940
McCaslin once commanded the Phillips Research Site at Kirtland, an Air Force base notorious

07:46.940 --> 07:49.880
for hosting advanced weapons research right nearby.

07:50.340 --> 07:52.060
He wasn't a stranger to this place.

07:52.300 --> 07:53.940
It was basically his backyard.

07:54.500 --> 08:00.360
His wife would also issue another statement, saying McCaslin had some risk, but not from dementia.

08:00.360 --> 08:02.960
He was not confused and disoriented.

08:03.400 --> 08:06.380
But a clear head didn't make him any easier to find.

08:06.640 --> 08:11.020
The Bernalillo County Sheriff's Office said that they had surveillance footage from both

08:11.020 --> 08:15.200
ends of his street and still couldn't confirm his direction of travel.

08:15.420 --> 08:20.100
They made public appeals for doorbell cameras, dashcams, GoPros, anything.

08:20.100 --> 08:25.600
If you have any information where McCaslin may be, contact BCSO's Missing Persons Unit.

08:25.760 --> 08:31.040
Within the span of a week, the search expanded from the Sheriff's Office to the FBI's Albuquerque

08:31.040 --> 08:36.300
Field Office to the Air Force Office of Special Investigations, New Mexico State Search and

08:36.300 --> 08:43.180
Rescue, Albuquerque Mountain Rescue, horseback teams, three types of search dogs, drones, helicopters,

08:43.180 --> 08:45.000
and neighborhood canvassing.

08:45.320 --> 08:50.580
And despite living in an era with enough cameras to catch almost every delivery on the block

08:50.580 --> 08:54.200
in which he lived, no footage of him ever surfaced.

08:57.000 --> 09:02.240
Police accessed his electronic devices and searched his usual hiking spots, like the

09:02.240 --> 09:05.180
Elenic Lagos area into the Domingo Baca Canyon.

09:05.740 --> 09:07.900
But there was still no trace of him.

09:07.900 --> 09:13.580
After weeks, all they could find was a gray Air Force sweatshirt a mile east of his house.

09:14.020 --> 09:17.900
And even after testing it, they couldn't confirm it was McCaslin's.

09:17.980 --> 09:23.820
So we're talking about a regimented, physically active military vet who vanished from his house

09:23.820 --> 09:27.620
without leaving a single digital or physical fingerprint behind.

09:28.780 --> 09:30.420
That alone is strange.

09:30.680 --> 09:35.960
But it gets stranger once you understand who McCaslin actually was and the world he came

09:35.960 --> 09:36.400
out of.

09:36.400 --> 09:39.700
General McCaslin, his disappearance was discussed.

09:39.880 --> 09:41.460
UAPs were discussed.

09:41.580 --> 09:44.000
So I don't think this story is going away, Jesse.

09:44.320 --> 09:49.400
This was a man who spent his career deep in the black world of American defense.

09:49.740 --> 09:55.140
When you read his official Air Force biography, you realize he had access to things that the

09:55.140 --> 09:58.060
rest of us aren't even supposed to know exist.

09:58.280 --> 10:02.540
The foundation for that kind of clearance started when he graduated from the Air Force

10:02.540 --> 10:09.320
Academy, earned a Ph.D. in Astronautical Engineering from MIT on a Hertz Foundation Fellowship, and

10:09.320 --> 10:11.600
later studied at Harvard's Kennedy School.

10:11.600 --> 10:17.700
He went on to lead the Space-Based Laser Project Office, served as vice commander of the Space

10:17.700 --> 10:23.340
and Missile Systems Center, was the Materiel Wing Director at the Air Force Research Lab's Space

10:23.340 --> 10:28.860
Vehicles Directorate at Kirtland, and spent part of his career in the National Reconnaissance

10:28.860 --> 10:32.640
Office, the world of black, off-the-record satellites.

10:32.640 --> 10:43.020
His career spanned everything from directed energy, to space weapons, to nuclear oversight.

10:43.860 --> 10:45.600
You probably get the point.

10:46.020 --> 10:51.460
This was a man who could out-credential most presidents, and probably had more access than

10:51.460 --> 10:52.060
them, too.

10:52.240 --> 10:56.220
And there are two jobs on his resume that matter more than the rest.

10:56.220 --> 11:03.280
From June 2009 to May 2011, McCaslin served as Director of Special Programs at the Pentagon,

11:03.840 --> 11:09.220
in the Office of the Undersecretary of Defense for Acquisitions, Technology, and Logistics.

11:09.800 --> 11:14.500
The title is a mouthful, but according to the official Pentagon training documentation,

11:15.200 --> 11:18.840
that office oversees acquisition special access programs.

11:19.260 --> 11:23.520
These programs are the ultimate category of secret black projects.

11:23.520 --> 11:30.960
In fact, they account for about 75 to 80 percent of all special access programs in the Department

11:30.960 --> 11:31.420
of War.

11:31.860 --> 11:35.220
These are the programs built to protect the crown jewels.

11:35.720 --> 11:40.860
Extremely sensitive research in the process of building something, like a next-generation

11:40.860 --> 11:45.160
weapons system, or a craft that doesn't officially exist.

11:45.440 --> 11:51.020
This is where sensitive technology moves from theory, to prototype, to something that the

11:51.020 --> 11:52.720
military can actually fly.

11:52.720 --> 11:58.420
And if you're wondering where UFO reverse engineering programs would possibly hide, this

11:58.420 --> 11:59.300
is the place.

11:59.680 --> 12:03.460
In the classified world, McCaslin's office was the motherlode.

12:03.780 --> 12:09.680
His Wikipedia page goes a step further, claiming that the role made him Executive Secretary of

12:09.680 --> 12:15.580
the Special Access Program Oversight Committee, the body that reviews and approves every single

12:15.580 --> 12:17.700
special access program in the Pentagon.

12:18.160 --> 12:21.160
But that's not even the most interesting job on his resume.

12:21.160 --> 12:31.500
From 2011 to 2013, McCaslin commanded the Air Force Research Lab, AFRL, at Wright-Patterson

12:31.500 --> 12:38.500
Air Force Base, overseeing a $2.2 billion science and technology portfolio, one of the largest

12:38.500 --> 12:41.240
research operations in the entire Pentagon.

12:41.240 --> 12:46.940
advanced material science, future weapons, and of course, exotic propulsion.

12:46.940 --> 12:51.960
And if you're familiar with UFO lore, you also know that Wright-Patterson isn't just

12:51.960 --> 12:53.620
famous for Project Blue Book.

12:54.080 --> 12:57.100
It's the alleged home of the Roswell crash debris.

12:57.100 --> 13:06.320
I called Curtis LeMay and I said, General, I know we have a room at Wright-Patterson where

13:06.320 --> 13:08.220
you put all this secret stuff.

13:09.720 --> 13:11.160
Could I go in there?

13:12.020 --> 13:17.120
I've never heard him get mad, but he got madder than hell of me.

13:17.480 --> 13:24.100
Depending on who you believe, this place houses some of the most exotic materials in the history

13:24.100 --> 13:25.420
of the U.S. government.

13:25.820 --> 13:31.100
It's the place where they get studied, stored, reverse-engineered, and obsessively hidden from

13:31.100 --> 13:31.860
public view.

13:32.180 --> 13:33.560
That's not even a conspiracy.

13:34.220 --> 13:39.960
This is the place during World War II where the U.S. would reverse-engineer advanced Nazi

13:39.960 --> 13:40.480
tech.

13:40.840 --> 13:43.940
And General Neil McCaslin ran the entire thing.

13:43.940 --> 13:55.260
But what really put him on the radar of UFO world is that his name showed up somewhere

13:55.260 --> 13:56.500
no one expected.

13:56.500 --> 14:03.080
In 2016, WikiLeaks published the hacked emails of John Podesta, Hillary Clinton's campaign

14:03.080 --> 14:07.380
chairman and one of the most powerful political operatives in Washington.

14:08.120 --> 14:12.840
Buried in that email dump is an email from Tom DeLonge to Podesta.

14:12.840 --> 14:15.680
The subject line, General McCaslin.

14:15.940 --> 14:16.840
DeLonge writes,

14:17.280 --> 14:19.080
He mentioned he's a skeptic.

14:19.380 --> 14:19.960
He's not.

14:20.120 --> 14:22.040
I've been working with him for four months.

14:22.280 --> 14:27.700
I've just got done giving him a four-hour presentation on the entire project a few weeks ago.

14:27.920 --> 14:32.120
He tells Podesta that McCaslin just has to say that out loud.

14:32.220 --> 14:34.180
Because he is very, very aware.

14:34.380 --> 14:37.480
Because he was the man in charge of all of this stuff.

14:37.620 --> 14:42.280
When Roswell crashed, they shipped it to the laboratory at Wright-Patterson Air Force

14:42.280 --> 14:43.120
Base.

14:43.120 --> 14:47.800
General McCaslin was in charge of that exact laboratory up to a couple years ago.

14:48.060 --> 14:52.840
He not only knows what I'm trying to achieve, he helped assemble my advisory team.

14:52.980 --> 14:54.840
He's a very important man.

14:55.140 --> 14:58.480
DeLonge was after UFO disclosure for the American people.

14:58.760 --> 15:01.100
That's the whole point of To the Stars Academy.

15:01.480 --> 15:05.540
General McCaslin being involved in those early efforts is a big deal.

15:05.540 --> 15:10.900
Some people try to dismiss Tom DeLonge and say that he was never in touch with Neil McCaslin.

15:11.300 --> 15:14.500
After all, these leaked emails were never publicly confirmed.

15:15.280 --> 15:20.800
But even his wife Susan would come to acknowledge that McCaslin was caught up in the Russian hack

15:20.800 --> 15:24.880
and had less contact with Tom after the emails were released.

15:25.400 --> 15:27.860
Key word here, less, not zero.

15:30.180 --> 15:34.500
And she's implicitly admitting that they were in close contact previously.

15:35.080 --> 15:41.720
In fact, in that same email batch that leaked, a calendar notification shows that Susan herself

15:41.720 --> 15:46.940
accepted a Google Calendar invite for something called a DeLonge-Podesta meeting.

15:46.940 --> 15:52.700
So at minimum, McCaslin and his wife were in the room for conversations about UFO disclosure.

15:53.040 --> 15:55.120
We're not talking about a 4chan thread here.

15:55.420 --> 15:58.320
We're talking about Podesta's actual inbox.

15:58.720 --> 16:02.880
And as for Susan McCaslin, she has a quite impressive background herself.

16:03.420 --> 16:07.620
She's a PhD astrophysicist, a colonel in the Air Force Reserve.

16:08.040 --> 16:13.780
She was a NASA astronaut semifinalist and had stints at both Boeing and Raytheon.

16:13.780 --> 16:17.480
She might even have her own clearance history.

16:18.600 --> 16:25.180
After McCaslin disappeared, she told the press that he only held commonly held clearances since

16:25.180 --> 16:25.700
retirement.

16:26.300 --> 16:26.580
Maybe.

16:27.320 --> 16:33.080
But a man who spent his career this deep in the black world likely saw the full portfolio.

16:33.440 --> 16:35.380
And you don't really unsee that.

16:35.640 --> 16:37.720
Susan later made a statement on Facebook.

16:37.720 --> 16:38.520
She wrote,

16:38.780 --> 16:43.760
Neil does not have any special knowledge about the ET bodies and debris from the Roswell

16:43.760 --> 16:45.580
crash stored at Wright-Patt.

16:45.660 --> 16:51.060
Though at this point, with absolutely no sign of him, maybe the best hypothesis is that aliens

16:51.060 --> 16:52.720
beamed him up to the mothership.

16:52.860 --> 16:57.880
However, no sightings of a mothership hovering above the Sandia Mountains have been reported.

16:58.140 --> 17:03.080
Maybe this is just a woman holding it together with dark humor while the internet tears her

17:03.080 --> 17:03.760
life apart.

17:03.940 --> 17:06.540
But it's undeniable that the phrasing is odd.

17:06.540 --> 17:10.820
She doesn't say Roswell material doesn't exist at Wright-Patterson.

17:11.120 --> 17:14.900
She just says McCaslin doesn't have any special knowledge about it.

17:15.100 --> 17:20.360
An event that, mind you, has been reported on ad nauseum in the open source world.

17:20.480 --> 17:21.820
So she might just be saying,

17:22.000 --> 17:26.920
there's nothing that Neil McCaslin knows about Roswell that you, the public, don't already

17:26.920 --> 17:27.220
know.

17:27.220 --> 17:33.540
Now look, any reasonable person should be hesitant to parse or speculate on the words

17:33.540 --> 17:34.740
of a grieving wife.

17:35.360 --> 17:38.600
And Susan and Neil deserve all of our thoughts and prayers.

17:38.960 --> 17:45.600
But also, to any reasonable person, these words almost feel like a cipher to decode, an

17:45.600 --> 17:48.440
invitation to speculate, just a little bit.

17:48.440 --> 17:52.260
And the statement ended up provoking just that.

17:52.720 --> 17:55.100
They spurred a lot of public speculation.

17:55.600 --> 17:58.700
If anything, the internet theorizing went into overdrive.

17:58.820 --> 18:07.460
I do think that there are secrets that obviously will not be released because we have technologies

18:07.460 --> 18:08.640
that other nations don't.

18:08.640 --> 18:13.200
and just see the superiority of our forces right now with Iran.

18:13.200 --> 18:19.660
Had McCaslin been quietly folded into some continuity of government program or taken into

18:19.660 --> 18:22.980
protective custody in preparation for the war with Iran?

18:23.320 --> 18:28.180
Had he been taken by a foreign adversary that understood exactly how valuable he was?

18:28.620 --> 18:35.500
People in UFO world associate McCaslin with the Majestic 12, an elite and top secret presidential

18:35.500 --> 18:41.200
advisory panel dating back to Truman and Eisenhower that deals with the UFO topic.

18:41.720 --> 18:47.220
There are a lot of reasonable questions as to whether this Majestic 12 committee ever really existed.

18:47.460 --> 18:52.280
But perhaps the person deepest on the UFO truth, at least from the government perspective

18:52.280 --> 18:58.040
that we know about over the last 70 years, is a guy named Colonel John Alexander.

18:58.040 --> 19:03.680
And at one point, he admitted that the Majestic 12 was basically just a cover for continuity

19:03.680 --> 19:05.140
of government programs.

19:05.500 --> 19:10.340
People in the military-industrial complex, where if the president and his direct cabinet

19:10.340 --> 19:12.900
were incapacitated, they would take over.

19:13.380 --> 19:17.160
To be honest, McCaslin sounds like he squarely fits that profile.

19:17.520 --> 19:20.300
Theories around his disappearance kept multiplying.

19:20.620 --> 19:23.460
And the timing of all of this didn't help either.

19:23.720 --> 19:24.680
Are aliens real?

19:24.680 --> 19:28.280
Uh, they're real, but I haven't seen them.

19:28.520 --> 19:34.620
In the summer of 2025, the mainstream Italian magazine, Let Espresso, published an article

19:34.620 --> 19:36.140
from a confidential source.

19:37.140 --> 19:43.020
It claimed that President Trump was wrestling control of special access programs away from

19:43.020 --> 19:47.860
the Pentagon and under the command of the White House, a move that supposedly sparked tensions

19:47.860 --> 19:51.820
between military leaders and some of the president's advisors.

19:51.820 --> 19:57.820
The article goes on to mention Project Preserve Destiny, a program involving communications

19:57.820 --> 20:03.040
with non-human intelligence housed under the National Security Agency, or NSA.

20:03.580 --> 20:08.700
The program involves some of the most bizarre protocols and has some of the most profound

20:08.700 --> 20:12.160
implications of anything we've ever covered on this show.

